    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "method='pad' is the same as method='fill', so in this case you were forward filling the last observable value over `nan` values.\r\n\r\n\t>>> df\r\n\t   Hello  Mad  World\r\n\t0    1.0  NaN    1.0\r\n\t1    2.0  NaN    2.0\r\n\t2    3.0  3.0    NaN\r\n\t3    NaN  4.0    NaN\r\n\t4    NaN  5.0    5.0\r\n\r\n\r\n\t>>> df['Hello'].replace(np.nan, None)\r\n\t0    1.0\r\n\t1    2.0\r\n\t2    3.0\r\n\t3    3.0\r\n\t4    3.0\r\n\tName: Hello, dtype: float64\r\n\r\n\t>>> df['Hello'].ffill()              \r\n\t0    1.0\r\n\t1    2.0\r\n\t2    3.0\r\n\t3    3.0\r\n\t4    3.0\r\n\tName: Hello, dtype: float64\r\n\r\n\r\nI can't remember the specifics of your original question, but `Series.replace(np.nan, None)` should behave the same as `Series.ffill()`"
  },
